# AXIS Task Routing

Classify every incoming task into exactly one category before proceeding.

## Categories

| Type     | Trigger keywords / signals                              |
|----------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| BUILD    | create, add, build, implement, new endpoint, new file   |
| FIX      | bug, broken, error, failing, not working, incorrect     |
| REFACTOR | restructure, clean up, rename, simplify, reorganize     |
| EXPLAIN  | what is, how does, explain, describe, show me           |
| CONFIG   | set up, configure, env, settings, install, permission   |

## Output of this step

State the classification explicitly before moving to decision.mdc:

```
[ROUTING] Type: <TYPE> | Complexity: <low|medium|high>
```

Complexity rules:
- low    — single file, no side effects, reversible
- medium — multiple files or external dependencies involved
- high   — destructive, cross-system, or ambiguous scope
